<div class="container marketing">

  <!-- Three columns of text below the carousel -->
  <div class="row"><a id="about"></a>
    <div class="col-lg-4">
      <img class="img-circle" src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/marcelandkim/wedding/abt-him-crop.jpg" alt="About Him" height="140" width="140">
      <h2>About Him</h2>
      <p>
        <!-- Button trigger modal -->
        <button class="btn btn-info" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#hisModal">
          View Details &raquo; 
        </button>
      </p>
  <!-- Modal -->
    <div class="modal fade" id="hisModal" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="myModalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
      <div class="modal-dialog">
        <div class="modal-content">
          <div class="modal-header">
            <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">&times;</button>
            <h4 class="modal-title" id="myModalLabel">About Him</h4>
          </div>
          <div class="modal-body">
            <p>
            It always seems like these things are kind of difficult to write, but here goes.
            </p>
            <p>
            After a few unsuccessful relationships, I decided that I would stop trying to find that right woman and just worry about myself.  Finding me, being me and loving me.  I figured that if I would do just that, the right person would come along and want the me that they see.
            </p>
            <p>
            Then, one sabbath afternoon, I pulled up into the church parking lot to see who was still at church.  And there she was, the woman that I knew of, but didn't really know.  I sat in the car and she offered to do my hair.  I happily obliged and we struck up a nice conversation.  I realized that even though I knew the person, I knew NOTHING of who this person was in front of me.  Our bond continued to grow and blossom over the course of a few years and I popped the question in front of her family before we went on our cruise.  It was a joyous occasion that I was elated to experience with the woman of my dreams.
            </p>
            <p>
            I love my roots (shout out to Jamaica and the Bahamas) and I love family.  I would probably say that is the thing I look forward to most about being married, is the ability to start our own family with the woman that I love.  All in all, I just hope to be a great husband and an even better father.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="modal-footer">
            <button type="button" class="btn btn-default" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
          </div>
        </div><!-- /.modal-content -->
      </div><!-- /.modal-dialog -->
    </div><!-- /.modal -->
    </div><!-- /.col-lg-4 -->
